Once the one-time cleansing is done, we recommended to the Management to:

1.	Instruct the General Services Officer to:

a.	Facilitate the procurement of supplies and PPE by issuing a PR at the beginning of the quarter in accordance with the Annual Procurement Plan of the LGU to avoid unavailability of stocks and consequent delay in the operations of the end-user units;

We recommended to the Management to:

1.	Direct the Municipal Accountant to record all purchases of supplies and materials in the proper inventory accounts; 

2.	Direct the GSO to consolidate weekly the RIS for which supplies and materials were issued using the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) and submit the SSMI together with the original copies of the RISs to the Municipal Accountant;

3.	Direct the Municipal Accountant to compute the cost of supplies issued and ending inventory using the moving average method upon receipt of the SSMI and RISs; and

4.	Direct the Municipal Accountant and GSO to regularly reconcile the balances of their ledger cards and stock cards to provide a reliable information on the existing inventories of the Municipality.

We recommended to the Management to:

1.	Direct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Engineer to coordinate as to the determination of the cost of ongoing projects as of year-end;

2.	Require the Municipal Engineer to submit to the Municipal Accountant’s Office a copy of the Consolidated Report on Government Projects/Programs/Activities (PPAs) for the fourth quarter as a reference for the status of ongoing and completed projects implemented by the LGU;

3.	Require the Municipal Engineer to submit to the Municipal Accountant’s Office a copy of the Statement of Work Accomplishment (SWA) for ongoing projects with unrecorded work accomplishments;

4.	Require the Municipal Accountant to record the unbilled and unrecorded work accomplishments of the ongoing projects in the accounting books at year-end upon receipt of the Statement of Work Accomplishment (SWA) from the Municipal Engineer’s Office; and 

5.	Submit a copy of the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) reflecting the year-end adjusting entries made together with the working paper and relevant supporting documents such as the Statement of Work Accomplishment (SWA) to the COA Office for verification.

We recommended to the Management to:

1.	Direct the MSWDO to submit justification as to the absence of supporting documents to the SACs;

2.	Direct the MSWDO to finally determine the list of beneficiaries and provide this office with a copy of the final masterlist file; 

3.	Direct the MSWDO submit a copy of the certified list from the DSWD; and

4.	Direct the Disbursing Officer to submit the acknowledgment receipts for the four (4) beneficiaries who were not able to sign the payrolls, otherwise, refund the amount of P24,000.00. Also, please submit to this office the certified true copy of the OR evidencing the refund.

We recommended to the Management to:

1.	Submit to the COA Auditor’s Office reasons for the non-compliance of the provisions of GPPB Circular No. 01-2020 explaining the legal basis upon which the LGU hinges its grounds for non-issuance of BAC resolution recommending award, Notice of Award, and Purchase Order; and

2.	For prospective purchases of goods,

a.	Direct the BAC to prepare and issue a resolution recommending award;

b.	Prepare and issue a Notice of Award upon recommendation of the BAC and have it received by the supplier;

c.	Prepare and sign a Purchase Oder which completely indicates the terms and conditions of contract and have it signed by the supplier before any delivery is made.

We recommended the management to:

a. 	Direct the Municipal Accountant to transfer the completed projects to its proper PPE Accounts and recognize the corresponding accumulated depreciation, and to submit to this office the journal entry vouchers and other necessary documents for the recognition of the completed projects;

b. 	Develop project monitoring and reconciliation procedures with the help of the Municipal Engineer and Municipal Accountant;

c. 	Direct the Municipal Engineer and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the above-identified projects; and

